org.readlogsfirst.api.logreader.logitemparser
Class LogParserContext<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

java.lang.Object
  org.readlogsfirst.api.logreader.logitemparser.LogParserContext<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
LogItemParser
public class LogParserContext<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements LogItemParser

A generic parser that uses four strategies to build up a LogLine structure. These four strategies are: LineTokenizer, which takes the full (multiline) log line as a string and knows how to split it into several tokens, no matter which is the meaning. It anyway knows tokens datatypes. IndexFinding, which given the list of tokens finds the one corresponding to the index (to be expanded in case of multi-index logs) LineFixer, which tries to fix lines in cases they are not compliant. It can have maning for complex structures log file types like weblogic one. ContentBuilding, which , given the list of tokens and the index, builds the LogLine.

Author:
fpacifici

Method Detail

parseLine

public LogLine<T> parseLine(java.lang.String item)
                                                     throws LogItemParsingException
Main algorithm to parse a log item (where an item can be a set of lines in the file identifying a log event. Parsing process goes through tokenizing the event. This generates a list of tokens. Extracting the index. If an indexer is not provided, the first token is considered as index. For some logs a fixer can be used to rebuild badly formatted lines. If the fixer is not present, no fixing is performed. Once this is done, the builder creates the log line to be returned starting from the tokens.

Specified by:
parseLine in interface LogItemParser
Parameters:
item - is the multiline or single line log event as got from the file
Returns:
the LogLine object. It is generic: the parameter is the type to be used as index.
Throws:
LogItemParsingException
